title Electrical Energy Storage & the Grid (April 2023)

// OWM coordinate convention: [visibility, maturity]
// visibility 0 = bottom of map, 1 = top (closest to user)
// maturity   0 = Genesis, 1 = Commodity

anchor Activity [0.97, 0.92]

// --- Demand side ---
component Consumers [0.92, 0.88]

// --- Core utility layer (what delivers electricity to activity) ---
component Electricity Generation [0.84, 0.86]
component Grid [0.82, 0.84]

// --- Grid models (the user asked for a traditional vs distributed contrast) ---
component Traditional Grid (single-machine view) [0.74, 0.72]
component Distributed Grid (fault-tolerant, TCP/IP-style) [0.74, 0.32]

// --- Control plane sitting under both grid models ---
component Control [0.66, 0.62]
component SCADA [0.58, 0.78]
component Auto Generation Control [0.56, 0.68]
component Spinning Reserve [0.52, 0.82]
component Fast-Response Systems [0.54, 0.55]

// --- Storage types (hydro / battery / hydrogen) ---
component Hydro Storage [0.46, 0.85]
component Electrical Storage (battery) [0.48, 0.62]
component Hydrogen Storage [0.44, 0.30]

// --- Energy platform & integration layer ---
component Energy Platform [0.40, 0.35]
component Integration Layer (pre-approval/discovery) [0.36, 0.18]
component Adaptive Integration [0.34, 0.14]
component Plug-and-Play Energy [0.32, 0.10]

// --- Underlying chain: sources, stockpile, supply chain, awareness ---
component Sources [0.26, 0.82]
component Stockpile [0.24, 0.70]
component Material Supply Chain [0.18, 0.30]
component Awareness of Energy Supply Chain [0.14, 0.12]

// ========= Edges (a -> b  means a depends on b; visibility(a) >= visibility(b)) =========

// Anchor to consumers to utility layer
Activity -> Consumers
Activity -> Electricity Generation
Consumers -> Grid
Consumers -> Electricity Generation

// Grid decomposes into the two competing grid models
Grid -> Traditional Grid (single-machine view)
Grid -> Distributed Grid (fault-tolerant, TCP/IP-style)

// Control sits under the grid
Traditional Grid (single-machine view) -> Control
Distributed Grid (fault-tolerant, TCP/IP-style) -> Control
Traditional Grid (single-machine view) -> SCADA
Traditional Grid (single-machine view) -> Auto Generation Control
Traditional Grid (single-machine view) -> Spinning Reserve
Distributed Grid (fault-tolerant, TCP/IP-style) -> Fast-Response Systems
Distributed Grid (fault-tolerant, TCP/IP-style) -> SCADA

// Generation leans on storage for balancing; storage leans on both grid models
Electricity Generation -> Hydro Storage
Electricity Generation -> Electrical Storage (battery)
Electricity Generation -> Hydrogen Storage
Grid -> Hydro Storage
Grid -> Electrical Storage (battery)

// Fast-response frequency services come from battery storage
Fast-Response Systems -> Electrical Storage (battery)
Spinning Reserve -> Hydro Storage

// Energy platform & integration layer sit between storage and the supply chain
Electrical Storage (battery) -> Energy Platform
Hydrogen Storage -> Energy Platform
Energy Platform -> Integration Layer (pre-approval/discovery)
Integration Layer (pre-approval/discovery) -> Adaptive Integration
Adaptive Integration -> Plug-and-Play Energy

// Underlying supply chain
Electrical Storage (battery) -> Material Supply Chain
Hydrogen Storage -> Material Supply Chain
Hydro Storage -> Sources
Electricity Generation -> Sources
Electricity Generation -> Stockpile
Sources -> Material Supply Chain
Stockpile -> Material Supply Chain
Material Supply Chain -> Awareness of Energy Supply Chain
Energy Platform -> Awareness of Energy Supply Chain

// ========= Movement =========
// Two headline movements the user asked to see:
//  1. distributed grid is accelerating past traditional grid
//  2. material supply chain is biting (accelerating but stuck left of where it needs to be)

evolve Distributed Grid (fault-tolerant, TCP/IP-style) 0.58
evolve Traditional Grid (single-machine view) 0.75 inertia
evolve Fast-Response Systems 0.68
evolve Electrical Storage (battery) 0.75
evolve Hydrogen Storage 0.45
evolve Energy Platform 0.55
evolve Integration Layer (pre-approval/discovery) 0.35
evolve Material Supply Chain 0.48
evolve Awareness of Energy Supply Chain 0.30
